HEADWORD: Calamistrum
<hw>Cal`a*mis"trum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
curling iron.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A comblike structure on the
metatarsus of the hind legs of certain spiders
(<fam>Ciniflonid⟦ae⟧</fam>), used to curl certain fibers in the
construction of their webs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calamite</ent>⟦br⟧
